The Emir of Kano, Alhaji Aminu Ado Bayero, on Saturday called on stakeholders in the tourism industry to sensitise and educate the public to appreciate domestic tourism and intensify engagement in airline operations to Kano. Bayero, who made the call at the North-West stakeholders’ forum held in Kano, also commended the Nigerian Tourism Development Corporation, for upgrading the tourism sector in the country. In his remarks on the occasion, the Director-General of Nigerian Tourism Development Corporation, Chief Folorunsho Coker, acknowledged that the digitisation of the Nigerian tourism industry had led to the flexibility of tourism business in Nigeria. Coker disclosed that digitalisation had enhanced competition in the industry thus creating opportunities for the digitally inclined, to earn more income. NTDC DG,  who was represented by Fibi Ikilama, Head of the National Travel Bureau, said the  priority of the forum, was to stimulate ideas toward enhancing further growth of the tourism industry.  Copyright PUNCH. All rights reserved. This material, and other digital content on this website, may not be reproduced, published, broadcast, rewritten or redistributed in whole or in part without prior express written permission from PUNCH. Contact: theeditor@punchng.com